programme.sub-title: A Whole New World & Bramble the Brave
programme.desc: Little Briar takes Vick’s axe and runs away with little Bramble. Vick follows them to the Pine Tree Kindergarten and meets many little animals there. Ms. Olivia tells him not to be afraid, and soon Vick gets along with the little animals there. Little Briar doesn’t want to join Vick and the other animals, seeming a bit lonely. Ms. Olivia then encourages little Briar to play with the others. At last, the kids at the kindergarten have a good time listening to Vick telling stories of the outside world.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.sub-title: Light Up, Little Guy & Happy Camping
programme.desc: The kids get in a cave of fireflies by chance, where they meet a firefly that can’t glow. They try to help it, but none of the methods work. Coach Mack tells them that a firefly takes in oxygen through air holes on its belly, and the more it takes in, the brighter the light it generates. By utilizing this principle, they encourage the little guy to light up at last.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.sub-title: A Bear’s Gotta Do What A Bear’s Gotta Do & The Watermelon Patch
programme.desc: Young Little Bramble is dependent on his brother doing everything, otherwise he’s gonna cry. Little Briar loves his little brother so he always makes a compromise. He takes him to school, lets him have the bigger apple, and win the game. In math class, Little Bramble is required to answer questions by himself. He fails and bursts into tears. After school, Little Bramble, who’s eager to catch up with Briar, walks home alone and works out math questions all by himself. Now he understands what his brother says, a bear’s gotta do what a bear’s gotta do.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.sub-title: Be Our Guest & Grow Bramble Grow!
programme.desc: Briar and Bramble invite Hoo Hoo to their lair. In order to treat their guest the best they can, they offer Hoo Hoo the best things they have, which turns out to be a great torture to Hoo Hoo instead. Hoo Hoo can’t stand it anymore and even finds herself unable to fly. Luckily, Mama Bear arrives home and saves her. She tells her sons --- Walk in others’ shoes, and then you’ll know what they really want. Then they provide Hoo Hoo with what she really needs, and have a wonderful dinner together.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Coach Mack teaches the kids not to open the door to strangers at class, and the next day, he disguises as a stranger to test the bear brothers. Mama bear cooperates with Coach Mack on the test and leaves home. Coach Mack tries various means to get the bear brothers to open the door, but to no avail. At last, the bear brothers pass the test.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: On the way to Mount Tai, Rascal finds an excuse to run away but Feral Knight gets him back in no time. When they walk up to a dumpling shop, Feral Knight asks Rascal to buy some dumplings without giving him money. Rascal has no choice but to steal a package of dumplings. Just then, the dumpling shop owner finds him and shouts “stop thief”. Feral Knight rushes to the shop owner’s aid and takes the rat together with dumplings away. Feral Knight throws a dumpling to Rascal and eats up the rest of them.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: Fierce the tiger admires the pupils in the Hands of Steel Academy and is simulating the movements in martial arts on the roof. However, he hits himself over the head with a broomstick by mistake and falls down from the rooftop. The master reads him a lecture and tells him to be a good cleaner. Despite the master’s instruction, Fierce never gives up his dream to become a martial artist. He is eager to prove himself a martial artist but is often more of a hindrance than a help.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: Guardian the horse is galloping across the forest to look for the Hands of Steel Academy. He comes to the summit of a mountain and gets lost. Meanwhile, Fierce is having lunch in the forest. Guardian smells a wonderful aroma of steamed buns and walks into the forest to search for them. Suddenly two hedgehogs stand in the way and wants to rob him of some valuables. They run after Guardian at his heels and order him to stop.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: The Kitchen God cannot drive the cloud teleporter and falls into the courtyard of the academy. He gets up and walks into the kitchen to check the hearth. At the same time, Fierce guides Guardian into the west wing room gingerly to show him Mazarine Jar, which however is discovered by the master. They are required to leave the Hands of Steel Academy at once. Guardian begs for the last dinner before leaving and the master agrees reluctantly. Then two animals enter the kitchen and make a fire to cook dinner.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.desc: The cubs break the trophy they won at the sports meeting. Fear of being criticized by Ms. Oliva, they make up a story that a blue bird attacks Briar and accidentally breaks the trophy. Ms. Olivia sees through their lie and gives them a lesson on honesty. The cubs confess their fault, and fix the trophy together.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.desc: Bramble decides to keep the caterpillar he finds on his head, and see how it grows up and becomes a butterfly. As time goes by, the caterpillar becomes a pupa, and soon it will turn into a butterfly. But in the process of metamorphosis, Bramble worries that it might get stuck, and tries to help. Ms. Olivia stops him and tells him that it needs to do it itself to get enough strength to fly. Just as they expected, the butterfly finally comes out, dries its wings, and flies.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.desc: The kids at Pine Tree Kindergarten are discussing what they want to be when they grow up. Vick says he wants to be an inventor and boasts that it’s easy to invent. To prove his point, he wants to invent something to dig holes as well as something for him to fly. However, both inventions meet with failure. Just when he is discouraged, he sees little Briar and Tiki playing paper planes. They are having a little contest. Then Vick gets an idea when he sees Bramble’s balloon. He attaches the balloon to the paper plane, and invents a “balloon plane” which could fly the most distance.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.desc: The cubs have got a new classmate – Ernie Jo, whose ears look different. A rumor starts that Ernie Jo’s big ears are infectious. Everybody tries to avoid him until Babu touches one of his ear by accident and he’s totally fine. The rumor is cleared and the cubs accept him. They invite Ernie Jo to play hide and seek. With the help of his big ears, Ernie Jo leads the cubs to find Little Vick who has fallen asleep and snores during the game. Now everybody wishes to have big ears like Ernie Jo’s do.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.sub-title: Rainy Day Fun & The More, The Better?
programme.desc: Violet hates rainy days. She doesn’t get why the others are having fun as usual. She tries to practice her flute, but rain drops cause her flute to get out of tune. Violet gets quite embarrassed and bursts into tears. To comfort her, everybody else gets busy doing funny tricks. Violet stops crying, asks why they enjoy the rain, and finds her own fun on rainy days.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: On the Same Page & Field Trip
programme.desc: Briar thinks Bramble is clumsy and can’t seem to cooperate with him well. The bear brothers have a match with Tiki and Babu. Tiki can eat the ice cream brought to him by Babu with his eyes closed, while Briar fails to eat the ice cream in Bramble’s hand. He feels even more frustrated when his face is smeared with ice cream. The cubs play a game after class. Briar still teams up with Bramble to get to the destination. However, Bramble falls behind. Briar chooses the path with apple trees at a junction in consideration of Bramble. When Bramble arrives at the junction, he thinks Briar would choose the bumpy path, and even sprains his ankles on the way. Luckily, Briar shows up just in time. They have a talk and finally understand that they love and know each other very well.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: The Hazelnuts & All by My Luna-Loo Lonesome
programme.desc: Tiki, Ernie Jo, and Violet are playing ball in the forest. Tiki happens to find a hazelnut tree when going to pick up the football. He climbs onto the tree to pick the nuts. The trio decide to get these hazelnuts to Violet’s home so her mom can crack them open. Briar and Bramble pass by and help them with the task. When they remove the shells of the hazelnuts, however, the cubs fight to get more of the nuts for themselves. Violet’s mom suggests using the hazelnuts to make a cake, and teaches them to share things with their friends.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: Clay Figure & The Toy Car Race
programme.desc: Pine Tree Kindergarten is hosting a handicraft show. Warren and Herbert ask Old Billy to teach them how to make clay figures for the show. Old Billy agrees. Herbert and Warren begin to prepare their clay figures for the show. However, Warren is lazy and skips many steps when making his clay figure. Herbert tells him to follow the steps, but he doesn’t listen. Warren’s figure cracks open during the show. He realizes that he can’t get lazy if he wants to do a good job.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: Tiki the Know-it-all & Warren the Chatterbox
programme.desc: The cubs go to harvest some vegetables. Tiki pretends to know everything and tells Babu that loofah is cucumber. Briar points out his mistake. Tiki tries to save face and tells Violet he can fix the dent in her tumbler. Tiki squishes the tumbler and only makes it worse. He sees Violet is really sad and realizes his mistake. Finally he asks Miss Olivia and learns about how to fix the toy.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker picks up a bouncy ball among the grass and takes it home. This small ball bounces around in a way that the frog cannot control. Joe Croaker now is standing on it and the bouncy ball begins to roll down a slope. The frog attempts tries to stop the ball but he simply is not able to mange. It takes the frog some agility and luck to avoid the rocks and tree branches in his way and finally he is stopped by one of McBroom’s dung balls.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Bartle Bee accidentally sets foot in a place studded with numerous full-blown flowers. Overjoyed, he plans to have a good time collecting nectar there. Then there comes a mean bee who tries to beat him up, accusing Bartle of trespassing on his turf. Intimidated, Bartle has to run away from that flourishing land. Flutterby learns of the whole story and decides to help her little buddy punish the bad bee. She paints two horrible huge eyes on the leaves and uses them to scare off the villainous bee. Then Bartle Bee sets up the leaves in the field, but a gust of wind blows them off to the ground, revealing the truth to the vicious bee. In his pursuit of Bartle Bee, the bully bee runs into a big bird which he believes to be a fake one for setting him up. He throws stones at the bird, only to be chased by the furious creature. Just when the bird is about to swallow him, Bartle Bee and Flutterby show up. They distract the bird and save the bee’s life. In the end, the three of them put behind the grudge and become friends.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker comes across a slingshot in the Marsh. He soon realizes that it is a decent swing. The frog then takes a thorough examination of the slingshot. He is convinced that he can shoot some pebbles with this new toy he just found. The pebbles cause damage to the neighboring insects and Joe Croaker could not stop there. He finds a box of pushpins and starts to shoot them.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Cosmo brags about seeing a long train in front of Joe Croaker. The fly can see the world from above in the mid air but Joe Croaker cannot. This upsets the frog. Joe Croaker figures that if he climbs up to the top of the tree, he will be able to get a better view there. But sadly for Joe Croaker, on a long list of the things he can achieve, climbing isn’t one of them. Advised by Cosmo, Joe Croaker makes many failed attempts to climb up the tree. First he tries to do it by sticking the double-sided tape to his limbs, which results in a heavy fall from the tree. Then Cosmo fetches him a rope with a big hook that is intended to be attached to the tree and help Joe up. But it falls and almost has Cosmo crushed. In the end, on Bartle’s suggestion, Cosmo helps Joe Croaker build up a firm ladder which Joe Croaker takes to reach the top of the tree. But when up there, Joe realizes that he is afraid of heights!

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.desc: Briar has a toothache and Vick tells him there are bugs eating his teeth, making him anxious. To get the bugs out, they try many methods, such as gargling water, asking Hoo Hoo to peck the bugs out, and singing to lure the bugs out, all of which are proven to be useless. At last, they go to see Nurse Beakman, then they find out the cause of tooth decay, and learn how to protect their teeth.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.desc: Violet has a treasure chest, inside which Luna-Loo likes the moon stone the most. That day, Luna-Loo hides the treasure chest somewhere else without Violet’s permission, but what she doesn’t know is that Ms. Lady Jane witnesses the whole thing. The cubs are busy helping Violet look for the chest, while Luna-Loo is invited to Ms. Lady Jane’s office, where she hears Violet’s words about how she cherishes the chest. Luna-Loo realizes what she has done is not right. Ms. Lady Jane comes in. She asks Luna-Loo to return a screwdriver to Vick, and tells her that even though she likes the screwdriver, she can’t keep it because she’s not the owner. Luna-Loo puts the chest back and makes a confession to her friends.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.sub-title: The Family Visit & You Get What You Put In
programme.desc: Little Briar misbehaves at kindergarten and refuses to apologize to the other kids. Ms. Olivia happens to go to the kids’ home for family visits. Briar is afraid that mom will learn about his behavior at kindergarten, so he tries various means to stop the family visit. Despite of this, Ms. Olivia still meets Briar’s mom. Seeing he could do nothing to stop the family visit, Briar tells the truth. Ms. Olivia tells Briar that he needs to confront his problems, and Briar learns a valuable lesson.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.sub-title: Tiki the Weatherman & Herby’s Helpful Apples
programme.desc: Old Billy forecasts the weather right, and Tiki asks Old Billy to teach him how to forecast a rainy day. Tiki makes notes and memorizes it. The other kids at Pine Tree Kindergarten plan to have a picnic, and Tiki tells them the weather will be sunny. However, just when the kids are going to have the picnic, it rains. Tiki goes to find Old Billy and asks him what’s wrong with the weather forecast. Old Billy explains that nature changes constantly and that only by studying hard could they make weather forecasts as accurate as possible.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.sub-title: Kitty the Tiger & The Magic Words
programme.desc: An uninvited guest, Kitty the tiger, sneaks into the drawing class, and shocks the whole class. But later this adorable tiger wins everybody’s heart. They like her, and volunteer to look after her. Kitty makes much trouble. However to make her happy, Prince Tiki lets her have his favorite bag. During naptime, kitty misses her mom so much that she can’t stop crying. Then the kids sing for her to help her sleep. It’s time to say goodbye. Everybody feels sad to part with her. Ms. Olivia promises that Kitty will attend the kindergarten when she grows up, making them happy again.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: Herbert on Ice & Warmth in Cold Winter
programme.desc: The forest is covered in snow in winter. Herbert always falls down on the slippery icy road. Vick takes him to learn skating from Coach Mack. However, Herbert is afraid he will fall down and doesn’t want to try. Luna-Loo let him sit on a chair. Herbert thinks it really fun to slide on ice. He tries to learn skating and finds out it’s not as hard as he has imagined. As he skates better and better, he finally understands things are not that difficult once he tries.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: Shadow has an extraordinary taste of tea and who at the same time an excellent brewer. She trains Hoffen to make him acquire the sixth sense. Hoffen spends a lot time watching Shadow brew wine since he finds it’s a little bit beyond him to acquire the subtle sixth sense. The other day Hoffen is lured into the Devoid Bamboo Bush by the two weasels. Star Kid here is completely lost there. He tries every possible direction but still can’t get out of the bush. Hoffen feels desperate when he hears his master’s sound, following which Hoffen finally acquire the sixth sense and walks out the mysterious bush.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: Hoffen and Rascal, under the instruction of Shadow, come all the way to Mount Crouch to locate his last master among the Circle of Twelve, Epsilon the dragon. They are not able to find the spirit of Epsilon rather than his real physical body. The dragon’s spirit is now called Traceless, who challenges Star Child in order to know thoroughly his kung fu skills. Hoffen convinces this mysterious master with a victory. Traceless tells Hoffen that he is trapped by Nian with a lock named Keyless. Hoffen is now determined to smash the lock to free Traceless.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: Hoffen is about to destroy the lock when the Enforcer appears. The crow tries to stop Hoffen but in vain. Hoffen is surprised to see the strange lock Keyless absorb his inner energy each time he hits it. Hoffen calms himself down before he finally finds the weakness of the lock. Star Kid smashes the lock and free Traceless from it. Traceless takes Hoffen to the hideout of Nian, where they can also expect Rascal, who let the weasels lead the way for him.

When they remove the shells of the hazelnuts, however, the cubs fight to get more of the nuts for themselves. Violet’s mom suggests using the hazelnuts to make a cake, and teaches them to share things with their friends.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac

Herbert tells him to follow the steps, but he doesn’t listen. Warren’s figure cracks open during the show. He realizes that he can’t get lazy if he wants to do a good job.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac

programme.desc: The cubs go to harvest some vegetables. Tiki pretends to know everything and tells Babu that loofah is cucumber. Briar points out his mistake. Tiki tries to save face and tells Violet he can fix the dent in her tumbler. Tiki squishes the tumbler and only makes it worse. He sees Violet is really sad and realizes his mistake. Finally he asks Miss Olivia and learns about how to fix the toy.

programme.title: Pondemonium

Joe Croaker now is standing on it and the bouncy ball begins to roll down a slope. The frog attempts tries to stop the ball but he simply is not able to mange. It takes the frog some agility and luck to avoid the rocks and tree branches in his way and finally he is stopped by one of McBroom’s dung balls.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Bartle Bee accidentally sets foot in a place studded with numerous full-blown flowers. Overjoyed, he plans to have a good time collecting nectar there. Then there comes a mean bee who tries to beat him up, accusing Bartle of trespassing on his turf. Intimidated, Bartle has to run away from that flourishing land. Flutterby learns of the whole story and decides to help her little buddy punish the bad bee. She paints two horrible huge eyes on the leaves and uses them to scare off the villainous bee. Then Bartle Bee sets up the leaves in the field, but a gust of wind blows them off to the ground, revealing the truth to the vicious bee. In his pursuit of Bartle Bee, the bully bee runs into a big bird which he believes to be a fake one for setting him up. He throws stones at the bird, only to be chased by the furious creature. Just when the bird is about to swallow him, Bartle Bee and Flutterby show up. They distract the bird and save the bee’s life. In the end, the three of them put behind the grudge and become friends.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker comes across a slingshot in the Marsh. He soon realizes that it is a decent swing. The frog then takes a thorough examination of the slingshot. He is convinced that he can shoot some pebbles with this new toy he just found. The pebbles cause damage to the neighboring insects and Joe Croaker could not stop there. He finds a box of pushpins and starts to shoot them.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Cosmo brags about seeing a long train in front of Joe Croaker. The fly can see the world from above in the mid air but Joe Croaker cannot. This upsets the frog. Joe Croaker figures that if he climbs up to the top of the tree, he will be able to get a better view there. But sadly for Joe Croaker, on a long list of the things he can achieve, climbing isn’t one of them. Advised by Cosmo, Joe Croaker makes many failed attempts to climb up the tree. First he tries to do it by sticking the double-sided tape to his limbs, which results in a heavy fall from the tree. Then Cosmo fetches him a rope with a big hook that is intended to be attached to the tree and help Joe up. But it falls and almost has Cosmo crushed. In the end, on Bartle’s suggestion, Cosmo helps Joe Croaker build up a firm ladder which Joe Croaker takes to reach the top of the tree. But when up there, Joe realizes that he is afraid of heights!

At last, they go to see Nurse Beakman, then they find out the cause of tooth decay, and learn how to protect their teeth.

Nice looking paint can’t hide the safety issues that are found once this car is put on the lift. From suspension, to brakes, to battery cables… and even down to the lug nuts, this auction beauty turns out to be more of a beast. Safety and sport-style handling are only a few repairs away this week on GearZ.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz

It’s simple gearhead stuff that everybody needs to know and it’s only on GearZ.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz

After that Stacey sits down with a budding car designer that is making a big impact everywhere he goes and there’s also a tip on the importance of seals and gaskets. It’s all about getting out and turning wrenches, and you’re only gonna find it on GEARZ!

A tip might keep you from losing your mind when dealing with lug nuts that don’t want to budge and we talk shop about performance parts for your own cars. So, come hang out while we take on a legendary cat of a different color this week on GearZ!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Stacey and the crew hit the ground running with a late model replacement bed from LMC that’s sure to revive and old Ford farm truck and get it out of the pastures and back on the highway. Then it’s off to show budding Jeep enthusiasts a couple of entry level options they can use when it comes to modifying their vehicle. We get a visit from a couple who learn how to install new seat upholstery. Stacey’s found something cool for all you second generation Camaro owners. And we’re just getting started! So get ready to turn some wrenches on GearZ.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: The GearZ crew and Cornwell Tools team up to help a new shop in Arkansas get some much-needed tools to help them take they’re shop the next level. Then it’s back to the shop to show you how easy it is to put fuel injection on your muscle car. It’s all here… and only on GEARZ!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Season 10 Starts off with America’s favorite military tribute truck! Sgt. Rock is back and ready for final assembly! Builders of all levels are in for a great show as Stacey tackles one of a kind steering columns, gas pedals and designing a console that not only fits form, but also function. programme.title: Caffeine & Octane
programme.sub-title: The Wrap on the Most Beautiful Cars

Caffeine and Exotics is featured again to show off the coolest wraps Atlanta can supply.

programme.title: Caffeine & Octane
programme.desc: Rickey and Bryan race outside of their comfort zones, each competing to find the raddest car collection. Mike takes Bryan motorcross racing in his backyard after showing off his high horsepowered car collection. The GT350R will hit the road with Operation Hope to encourage young people to study math and science through motorsports; Covert car counterfeiter, Chuck Beck looks for Ford’s approval on his own version of a muscled up Festiva. YouTuber ‘That Dude in Blue’ David Patterson joins Skip and Bryan to get a special look at the motor-based philanthropic outreach and amazing cars that come with it done by John Hope Bryant, friend of Caffeine and Octane.

programme.title: Truck U

programme.title: Truck U
programme.desc: This fleet F150 needs a kick into high gear. We’ll give the truck some needed stopping power with an upgraded brake kit and we’ll bolt on some power upgrades under the hood.

programme.title: Truck U

programme.title: Truck U

programme.title: Truck U

programme.title: Truck U

programme.title: What's In the Barn?
programme.desc: An family farm in the mid-west contains houses, barns, outbuildings, trailers, grain silos and buses full of old stuff and perhaps the biggest stash of undiscovered old motorcycles in the country. The collection was put together by their unnamed father. Seller agrees to have Dale broker rare Excelsior for high-end client. Dale has the buyer, but will he outbid his own client for the exclusive find?

programme.title: What's In the Barn?
programme.desc: Matt is out for revenge. Last year Dale beat him badly at the Annual Vintage bike race in Barber, Alabama. But this year there is a whole new tale to tell. With just days until the race - Dale is secretly struggling to get the bike he beat Matt with last year up and working. Matt struggles just to locate a 100-year old bike. Matt's prayers are answered thanks to an old Catholic Priest he located who has possession of a bike. The priest might let Matt have the bike to race - but there are conditions. The toughest one: Don't tell Dale you have it. Can Matt afford to buy the bike and get it running in time for the race without Dale seeing it? Will Dale even get his broken bike started? And if they ever get to race, will Matt exact his revenge?

programme.title: What's In the Barn?
programme.desc: Built in the mid-60’s by eccentric engineer “Wild Bill” Gelbke, the Road Dog was, and still is, the largest motorcycle ever built. It utilized aircraft tubing, Corvette disc brakes, and a Chevy truck differential to keep it stable. The one-off creation disappeared when Gelbke did in 1978. Outflanked once when the bike was spotted and sold to a private collector in 1995, Dale has vowed to locate the machine and make Wheels Through Time its final resting place.

programme.title: What's In the Barn?
programme.desc: Big Time Motorcycle Auction

programme.title: What's In the Barn?
programme.desc: The RM Auction Company has worked with Dale before as a buyer, seller, historian, and caretaker at the prestigious Lee Hartung auction. But this event is no last minute rush to define one man’s treasures. This is a well calculated, time consuming, multi-media, and multi motorcycle and prized art deal.

programme.title: What's In the Barn?
programme.desc: Home Depot Senior Vice President, Gordon Erickson, is a huge fan of Wheels Through Time. He is also a huge supporter of the Wounded Warrior program. For years the hardware giant has been donating goods and services to help returning servicemen with their fix-it-up projects. Now they would like to go one step further and build a WWII military bike to raise awareness and funds. Only problem is where to get one? Enter Dale and an exhaustive, time sensitive, cross country search for a rare military machine.

programme.title: What's In the Barn?
programme.desc: Promoters of the prestigious Amelia Island Concours have called on Dale to develop a show and field bikes for an “Orphan Bike” show. They have defined orphan bike as extremely rare, that aren't a Harley nor Indian machines.

programme.title: What's In the Barn?
programme.sub-title: Time is Not On Their Side
programme.desc: For Dale and Matt sometimes the dotted line to treasure splits and heads in opposite directions. In this edition of What’s in the Barn, time is thrust to the forefront of this multi-state, long distance, north, south search. Timeless and priceless 110 year old bikes, antique cars, airplanes, and the infamous Egberts 1930 neon Harley-Davidson sign that coined the phrase “Ride a Winner” are high on this father and son’s list of “must haves”. The clock ticks, both literally and figuratively, on one rare time piece and two old-timer’s cars, bikes, and automobiles.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: A custom build can lose some power if the theme doesn’t stay consistent. Stacey shows how to do that by taking you through the process of how to make door and kick panels that keep the rugged military WWII bomber vibe flowing throughout the interior of Sgt. Rock. After that, its some tips on how to fit a radiator and that all-important cooling fan in a place where space is limited. Finally, the gas tank and battery placement are critical on a custom vehicle and Stacey goes through the steps in doing that as well. If you’ve always wanted to build a custom vehicle, this episode is sure to get your fabrication gearZ turning.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Two things are certain in life: death and taxes. We all know what to do with taxes, but what happens when a loved one passes and leaves behind an unfinished project vehicle? How do you know what’s sitting in your garage? And how can you find out? Stacey tackles these questions and takes you on a thorough inventory of an almost finished restoration that was left to a widow when her husband suddenly died. A new dash going into your vehicle? A gauge tech should keep you from crossing your wires. And we’ve got tips that should help with battery relocation and lining up your vehicle’s body panels.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.sub-title: Gearz On The Road - Basic Tools
programme.desc: The GearZ crew mount up and head out to visit a young gear-head whose love of wrenching started with 4-wheelers and has grown to include 4-wheel drive pick ups. Young Adam has a few surprises in store as Stacey visits him in his Dad’s garage and discusses tools, storage and tearing apart things to see how they work. Then, it’s back in the shop as Stacey takes on the big question every gear-head has: What OTHER tools should I have in my box? A look beyond the typical wrenches, hammers and clamps will show you what you may need and what you may not, depending on your project.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.sub-title: Cheetah Body Work Latches Custom Exhaust
programme.desc: The son of legendary car builder, Bill Thomas, talks shop about wrenching, racing and his father’s Cobra Killer…the Cheetah. Then Stacey heads over to Stainless Works to check out how the Cheetah’s custom side pipes, headers and mufflers came together. A Gauge Tech explains the pros and cons of mechanical vs. electric gauges. After that, a Quick Tip explains the proper way to use some of those mystery tools laying around in your tool box.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Ever wonder why your wife or best buddy won’t step foot in your late model truck? It could be that crusty interior. Tag along as Stacey takes on the sights and smells of an ’83 Chevy in dire need of some attention. From new dash to leather on the bench seat and new carpet in the floor, Stacey shows you what a difference a weekend and some parts from LMC can make. Speaking of trucks, Stacey raises the bar with a bed lifter that will make you the most popular guy in your neighborhood. A new buffer is going to help add some shine to your vehicle and a creeper that’s simply “Magic” is sure to raise an eyebrow or two. Big things are happening in the garage this week on GearZ.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Through the years, we’ve had some amazing vehicles featured on GearZ—from elite racecars to the insanity of a V-8 barstool. Well, here we go again! Stacey hauls in a Thiokol Imp that needs some…attention. First things first with this crazy snowcatmobile; we’ve got to see if we can make it run. Follow along as Stacey takes you through the ins and outs of getting a neglected vehicle up and running again. For you performance BMW guys, a tuner from Dinan is going add the horses you’ve been looking for. We’ve got sparks flying, fuel splashing and all kinds of garage mayhem this week on GearZ.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: In the world of car building there are few things more ominous than missing titles or VIN numbers. But there is one task that stands out, one that brings grown men to tears, one that is usually lurking behind 100 yards of electrical tape…WIRING. Well hold on tight as Stacey dives head first into wiring Sergeant Rock. That’s right; see how painless Stacey can make wiring the big old truck. Follow along as Stacey moves front to back and gets the Rock one step closer to hitting the road!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: With summer in full swing, it’s time to cool down that classic truck of yours. That’s right, roll those windows up and feel the cool breeze as Stacey shows just how easy it is to install this complete AC system from LMC Truck. Now that you’re done sweatin’, let’s take a look at headers and intakes and get that motor performing the way it should. And don’t miss out on the ins and outs of turbos and super-chargers…which one fits your needs? All this and plenty of sparks in the garage this week on GearZ.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Stacey and the GearZ crew heat things up as they head to the Cornwell forges to watch molten steel be expertly transformed into America’s best ratchet. Get ready to see sparks fly. But the trip doesn’t stop there. Tag along as the crew follows what it takes for a ratchet to end up on a Cornwell truck. Back in the garage, Stacey talks maximizing boost and the role of intercoolers when it comes to super-chargers and turbos. The wheels keep turning and the rubber keeps burning, this week on GearZ.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Cheetah lovers will be excited to see Stacey’s solution to keeping the headers both cool and looking red hot. Want to keep using your stock tank after converting to fuel injection? Get psyched, because Holley has a new fuel pump that’s going to make your life a whole lot easier. Think your car is buttoned up tight? Stacey and some friends from Redline Detection blow smoke at the old soap and water test and show you how to really test for leaks in your vehicle. It’s a world of problems out there, but Stacey’s got you covered in the garage. All this and more, this week, on GearZ.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: This week Stacey and crew head to Memphis, TN to help out a local BBQ pitmaster who’s deep into a ground up rebuild of a ’72 Nova. The big challenge here?...Can you swap out an automatic transmission with a manual without losing your mind? Well, Stacey is always up for a good challenge and he’ll show you just how simple this swap can be. A new tuner from Super chips will make your Jeep life easier, and replacement dashes for Chevy owners are going to light up their eyes. There’s a lot going on in the garage this week on GearZ.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.sub-title: Cheap Fuel Injection Snow Cat Bed TN Electric Guitar
programme.desc: We’re winding up the tenth season of GearZ, and what a season it’s been! But we’ve got some business to take care of before we move onto season eleven. First things first…Holley just made an EFI even easier to install on your carbureted vehicle, and Stacey will show you just how on target the Sniper is. The Thiokol Imp gets a suspension upgrade to keep it on track. And there’s a new kind of off-roading that’s sweeping the nation…see what RC4WD has going on. And what season would be complete without guitars? Check out Tennessee Electric Company as Stacey introduces a new guitar-maker whose custom guitars are hotter than the asphalt at the drag strip.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: We’re back and taking it to the streets! Season 11 comes roaring back with a look at Super Lite Cars on the road and the track! Stacey recalls and earlier SLC build and introduces two SLC builders who took a very hands-on approach to putting their cars together. These street/race cars are sure to catch your eye and get your racing blood flowing. If there’s one thing Stacey preaches on every episode, it’s paying attention to the details. His quick tip is no exception, getting rid of those sharp edges and nasty welds to give your project the small details that people will notice. Side mirrors for a muscle car, building a better battery, and keeping your air flowing through carbon fiber vents fill out the parts bin. We’ve got all this and more as Stacey kicks of his 11th season of GearZ!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: This is the moment you’ve been waiting for! Master car builder, Stacey David, shows off the truck that’s had the nation talking for ten years! Take a look back at the kid with the dream. Follow the design and fabrication. See what happens when the military tribute vehicle rolls out and conquers the road! This episode is gonna be epic. It’s been a long road, but anything worth doing well is worth the wait. This week, the wait is over. Sergeant Rock Lives!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.sub-title: On the Road & Unicure Spray Booths
programme.desc: Things are rockin’ and rollin’ in and out of the GearZ garage. Stacey hits the road to find a project build that will get gear heads buzzing. He ends up with an ’81 Camaro and some awesome stories from the seller. If you’re talking project vehicles, you’ve got to talk paint! And Stacey does just that with folks from Unicure, who specialize in paint booths and helping you get set up for that all important paint job. The V-8 Interceptor is back from a trip to Stainless works, where a custom exhaust system was made for the big Boss Nine engine. Things are about to get loud, this week on GearZ.

programme.desc: Scaredy Smurf runs into the Village screaming about the sky being about to smurf down. And just at the same moment, Papa Smurf is beset by uncontrollable fits of sneezing...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Papa instructs adult Smurfs (Nat, Snappy and Slouchy) to deliver an hourglass to Father Time. While there, the three step inside a clock which is running backwards and they go back in time. Father Time says there is no way to make them older. All must accept them as Smurflings and learn that they have a lot to offer.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Everybody can make a mistake. Take Papa Smurf, for instance. His new perfume-enhancing spray makes a rose smell like a thousand roses...but due to a whole series of misadventures it also makes all the Smurfs cry, moved to tears by the slightest of pretexts. While they sob, bawl, wail moan and whimper, the evil wizard Gargamel does not stand still...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Handy gives Smurfette a pair of rose-colored glasses that are instrumental in luring her into Gargamel's clutches. Fortunately, a hungry giant comes visiting, tries the glasses on, which make Gargamel look very appetizing. As he chases the wizard, the Smurfette escapes.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: When the Smurfs reach Ancient China, they learn that the child Emperor is in danger of being deposed, and by whom? By the evil Garg-Fu-Yun, who wants to rule in the child's stead!

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The evil Maestro's magical paints have the power to transport his models onto canvas – forever! Papa Smurf directs Painter to switch his paints and before long, Maestro is enshrined in a picture next to his dream girl, Smurfette.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Dreamy's wish of becoming an Astrosmurf comes true when Papa Smurf puts him to sleep, magically transforming the landscape and the Smurfs into a space fantasy. Gargamel keeps a close watch on their antics through his crystal ball, but he too falls victim to Papa Smurf's magic and is sent into a thunderstorm.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Gargamel the evil wizard is in trouble again. If he can't find an enormous amount of gold by sundown, all his possessions will be taken away from him. But the Smurfs are going to help their arch-enemy... Up to a point.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: In the depths of the rain forest, the Smurfs meet with a headhunter who shrinks their skulls and changes them into pinhead idiots. Clumsy is able to escape, and matters come to a head.

programme.title: All Creatures Great And Smurf
programme.desc: Nat Smurf is convinced he can help all creatures with his healing ways, even the wicked Azrael after he gets his paw caught in a trap. He heals well, but even though he is tempted to stay with the Smurfs, he runs back to Gargamel while leading his old master away from Smurf Village.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Posing for a sculpture, especially a huge composition like that of Painter Smurf, is very tiring work, and you can't help moving a little. Now Papa Smurf finds a way to keep the posers perfectly still. There are drawbacks though, as the Smurfs will soon realise...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Their magic crystals make the Smurfs really go places. Here they are in Antarctica, freezing themselves blue, and baby Smurf catches cold. How can they escape to a warmer climate?

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Papa Smurf's growth potion is accidentally spilled on a Howlibird that grows into a giant creature. After much thought, Papa Smurf uses his anti-growth formula on the bird and soon it and the Smurf village return to normal.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Smurfette discovers the evil with Chlorhydris's wicked plan to cast "a world without love" spell at the magic wishing well. It's a race against time for the Smurfs and Cupid to save the day!

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: What is that strange talking frog that Morlock the Wizard sends all of Prince Theodore's soldiers to catch? Is it a demon frog, as he says, or something else? Truth will out when Smurfette and the Smurflings meet the frog. They help to change this frog back into Prince Theodore himself, for he's been the victim of a spell cast by Morlock.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: There is a prize for the cutest pet of a Smurf. Baby Smurf brings a cute, lovely, affectionate Glowing Darling, a pet anybody falls in love with... But this pet is a creation of Gargamel, the evil wizard intent on destroying the Smurfs!

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Una hermosa princesa resulta transformada en una bruja y necesita los bigotes de un gato y la lagrima de un Pitufo para preparar una pocion magica. Azrael, Pitufo Grunon y Pitufo Bromista se convierten en colaboradores involuntarios y, cuando se produce la transformacion magica, la princesa les libera y regresan felices a su hogar.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Armonia ya no es bienvenido en el coro de los Pitufos: canta de una manera demasiado desafinada. Sin embargo, Papa Pitufo le entrega un amuleto que le convertira en un virtuoso del canto. Y, por si fuera poco, aqui llega Hogata...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Fortachon se disfraza de Pitufina para atraer a Piltkin, el gnomo que se ha enamorado de ella, y alejarlo de la Aldea Pitufa. Excavan bajo tierra y conocen a una gnoma que se enamora de Piltkin, quien se olvida de Pitufina y pasa a tener ojos solo para su nueva conquista.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Gargamel y Baltasar se ponen a los mandos de un Robotin gigante para obligar al rey Gerard a que les entregue a Pitufo Robotin. Cuando el Robotin esta a punto de destruir el castillo, Giganton, el nuevo, enorme y extrano amigo de Pitufo Robotin, vence al Robotin. Pitufo Robotin sufre danos durante la batalla, pero Pitufo Carpintero lo arregla y le implanta una caja de voz que le permite decir «¡Hola!».

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Te despiertas temprano por la manana, antes de que los demas Pitufos se hayan levantado de sus camas, para preparar sabrosos bizcochos de pitufrutas. Dedicas toda la manana a preparar pitufimanjares para el almuerzo. Despues, toda la tarde a tener la deliciosa cena lista a tiempo. ¿Y acaso los demas Pitufos te dan siquiera las gracias? Asi pues, Pitufo Goloso renuncia. La aldea esta en problemas... y pronto, tambien lo esta Pitufo Goloso.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cuando el hada de las flores aparece en el pueblo de los Pitufos, todos se enamoran de su encanto e inteligencia. Y pronto se daran cuenta de que se convertira en una especie de mama pitufo para todos...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos llevan a Abuelo Pitufo al castillo del rey para que pueda conocer a Guillermo. Pero, entre una cosa y otra (sobre todo otra), los Pitufos y Guillermo acaban a bordo de una gran nave vikinga. Los vikingos creen que Guillermo es su mitico gran guerrero, aquel que derrotara al Rey Tormenta. ¿Podran los Pitufos ayudar a Guillermo a salir de este embrollo?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: En lugar de insistir con su poesia, ya que nota que ninguno de los Pitufos la escucha, Pitufo Poeta decide escribir un libro. Y acaba de encontrar el material perfecto: un libro en blanco con una hermosa cubierta en el que comienza a verter su imaginacion. Entonces, en la aldea comienzan a suceder cosas extranas...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Si hay algo que la malvada hechicera Clorhidris no puede soportar es la felicidad de las demas personas. Contemplar la vida de los Pitufos, llena de amabilidad y canciones, pone furiosa a Clorhidris. Debe destruir esas risas y ahogar esas felices conversaciones... Entonces, planta la raiz del mal en el bosque y, poco despues, todos los Pitufos dejan de hablarse. El unico que no se ha visto afectado es Bebe Pitufo...

programme.title: El Pitufo Enmascarado
programme.desc: Una noche de Luna Azulada, tal y como la leyenda decia, un bebe pitufo aparece en el pueblo, y todos acaban agarrandole carino. Pero todo ha sido un malentendido y la ciguena vuelve por el bebe. Pintor y Grunon se han encarinado tanto con el bebe que les regresan al bebe.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Es la noche de los fantasmas y todos los Pitufos se preparan para la elegante fiesta de disfraces... pero Pitufo Filosofo se hace con el libro de magia de Papa Pitufo y todos los Pitufos se transforman en criaturas horrendas, aunque divertidas. No obstante, el peligro acecha...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: Viaje Al Pitufo De La Tierra
programme.desc: El invierno ha llegado a la Aldea Pitufa. Y los pequenos Pitufos estan helados de frio. ¿Pero que esta haciendo Pitufo Torpe con esa extrana roca que ha descubierto? ¿Y por que esta tan entusiasmado Pitufo Minero con su nuevo descubrimiento? Nadie entiende a que se debe tanto revuelo por una simple nueva roca para la coleccion de Pitufo Torpe... Al adentrarse bajo tierra, los Pitufos encontraran peligros y sorpresas.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: Una Fiesta De Pijamas Para Perezoso
programme.desc: ¡Pobre Pitufo Perezoso! Todo lo que desea es una buena noche de descanso. Pero no: todos los Pitufos celebran una fiesta en su honor y, lo que es peor, se ve arrastrado a una absurda discusion sobre pintar los dedos de los pies de Giganton de un brillante color mandarina. ¡Va a ser una larga noche en vela para el pobre Pitufo Perezoso!

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Esta vez, Gargamel se siente seguro de si mismo. Bueno, casi... ¡Esta a punto de atrapar a los pequenos Pitufos! Las ligerisimas tortitas de Pitufo Goloso casi provocan que los Pitufos floten hasta quedar al alcance de Gargamel.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Hogapatra, la espantosa, hinchada y vulgar reina del Nilo, no puede dormir y eso hace que le aparezcan grandes ojeras. Su receta para la belleza incluye exprimir a Pitufo Perezoso para extraerle sueno...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: Escrupulo Y El Libro De Los Hechizos
programme.desc: Cuando Escrupuloso, el ayudante del malvado Gargamel, encuentra el Gran libro de hechizos en el sotano de su maestro, le pide poder para convertirse en el mago mas poderoso del mundo. Y esto supondra problemas para los pobres Pitufos...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: Todo Esta Bien Si Termina Bien
programme.desc: El robo del oro de las hadas por parte de Gargamel casi lleva a la guerra a los Pitufos con las hadas.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Genio inventa a Pituforobotin para que ayude a todos los Pitufos en sus labores, pero Filosofo lo reprograma para que abandone la Aldea Pitufo.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Aqui viene de nuevo Pitufo Filosofo. Bebe Pitufo se pierde mientras estaba a cargo de Pitufo Torpe, y Pitufo Filosofo insiste en que es necesario celebrar un juicio. ¿Como podra defenderse el pobre Pitufo Torpe? ¿Y como ha omitido Pitufo Filosofo que el era originalmente el encargado de cuidar de Bebe Pitufo? ¿Como terminara este embrollo?

programme.title: El Dia Libre De Papa Pitufo
programme.desc: Los Pitufos deciden que Papa Pitufo necesita un descanso, por lo que acuerdan resolver sus problemas sin su ayuda. Papa Pitufo se siente inutil, pero Omnibus, su sabio amigo, le muestra que los Pitufos no podrian arreglarselas sin el. Papa Pitufo regresa justo a tiempo para arreglar una presa que tiene fugas, y se siente util de nuevo.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cuando una gota de la nueva pocion de Papa Pitufo cae en el libro de aventuras de los Pitufitos, el heroe de ficcion cobra vida. El intrepido Don Pitufo, que desea deshacer a los Pitufos del malvado Gargamel, lo captura con valentia...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: El Dia de los Inocentes Pitufo resulta no ser tan divertido cuando Gargamel se pone un disfraz de Pitufoarbusto para capturar al pequeno Pitufo Feliz. Papa Pitufo pide ayuda a Pitufopluma para que llame a los pajaros y ataquen al falso arbusto.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Tenia que pasarle a Pitufo Filosofo. La quintaesencia de la pitufietiqueta, el epitome de la correccion, la personificacion de todas esas virtudes es, asumamoslo, aburrido y pretencioso. Y ahora, Pitufo Filosofo sufre la agonia de volverse... digamos que diferente. Sin embargo, esta en grave peligro...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Genio ha decidido dedicarse al bienestar de los demas Pitufos. Va a curarles de todos sus males...con la ayuda del malvado Gargamel!

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: En Egipto hay un faraon gato llamado Azrael, un nombre que resulta familiar a los Pitufos. ¡Y lo mismo sucede con el nombre del cruel capataz! Gargahotep quiere esclavizar a los Pitufos para construir una piramide...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: La primavera provoca que todos los Pitufos esten compitiendo por el amor de Pitufina y Gargamel decide hechizarla para que le ayuda a capturarlos. Papa Pitufo toma cartas en el asunto y con la ayuda del despistado gato Azrael consigue darle la vuelta al plan.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos y Omnibus se hacen amigos de un desdichado joven cuyo maestro le obliga a robar. Pronto, el malvado ladron es entregado al magistrado y el joven esta encantado de irse a vivir con Omnibus.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Gargamel esta decidido a sobrevolar la Aldea Pitufa para atrapar a un Pitufo y llevarlo a la Convencion de los Magos, e invoca a su libro de hechizos para que le ayude. Esto da lugar a una serie de divertidos contratiempos con su maquina voladora, y Gargamel vuelve a convertirse en el hazme reir de la Convencion de los Magos.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Una hermosa princesa resulta transformada en una bruja y necesita los bigotes de un gato y la lagrima de un Pitufo para preparar una pocion magica. Azrael, Pitufo Grunon y Pitufo Bromista se convierten en colaboradores involuntarios y, cuando se produce la transformacion magica, la princesa les libera y regresan felices a su hogar.

programme.title: Pituplicacion
programme.desc: El malvado mago Gargamel crea una formula magica que duplica todo aquello que toca. Y...¡sorpresa! ¡Ahora hay seis Pitufos Filosofos! Esto provoca algunas situaciones interesantes en la aldea... ¡Y tambien en casa de Gargamel!

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos descubren una Fuente de la Juventud cuidada por un espantoso Troll que roba el libro magico de Papa Pitufo.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Te despiertas temprano por la manana, antes de que los demas Pitufos se hayan levantado de sus camas, para preparar sabrosos bizcochos de pitufrutas. Dedicas toda la manana a preparar pitufimanjares para el almuerzo. Despues, toda la tarde a tener la deliciosa cena lista a tiempo. ¿Y acaso los demas Pitufos te dan siquiera las gracias? Asi pues, Pitufo Goloso renuncia. La aldea esta en problemas... y pronto, tambien lo esta Pitufo Goloso.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cuidar de los animales produce consecuencias inesperadas cuando los Pitufos deciden llevar a un bebe dinosaurio de vuelta a casa... ¡a su propia era! Este es el inicio de una serie de aventuras en las que recorreran el espacio y el tiempo.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Una vez al ano, Pitufo Goloso prepara un lote especial de caramelos de pitufrutas. Cada Pitufo recibe provisiones para un ano entero del dulce mas pitufantastico de todo el mundo. Pero ¿puede un Pitufo conseguir que sus provisiones le duren todo el ano? ¿Lo conseguira Pitufina?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufitos acompanan a Pitufo Lanudo en su mision de esquilar ovejas para obtener lana para la ropa de invierno. Deben superar varios obstaculos, como Gargamel, un lobo y, por ultimo, un pastorcillo que no acepta pitufrutas como pago por la lana. El respeto mutuo entre los Pitufitos y Pitufo Lanudo va creciendo a lo largo del viaje.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Gargamel esta decidido a sobrevolar la Aldea Pitufa para atrapar a un Pitufo y llevarlo a la Convencion de los Magos, e invoca a su libro de hechizos para que le ayude. Esto da lugar a una serie de divertidos contratiempos con su maquina voladora, y Gargamel vuelve a convertirse en el hazme reir de la Convencion de los Magos.

programme.title: Simbolos De Sabiduria
programme.desc: Pitufo Filosofo esta desesperado por parecerse mas a Papa Pitufo. ¿Podria ser la respuesta un tonico capilar? ¿Conseguira Gargamel capturar por fin a los Pitufos? ¿Reside realmente la sabiduria en una barba?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Sonador desea encontrar vida extraterrestre pero en la Aldea se burlan de el. Nadie le creera cuando les diga que ha hablado con un ser de otro planeta.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Unos lentes rosados llegan a manos de Pitufina y resultan ser un sucio truco de Gargamel.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Filosofo y Bebe Pitufo mezclan las formulas de Papa Pitufo con consecuencias desastrosas, dejandoles a merced de un ejercito de hambrientas langostas que Gargamel ha soltado en el bosque.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Es la noche de los fantasmas y todos los Pitufos se preparan para la elegante fiesta de disfraces... pero Pitufo Filosofo se hace con el libro de magia de Papa Pitufo y todos los Pitufos se transforman en criaturas horrendas, aunque divertidas. No obstante, el peligro acecha...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Genio ha decidido dedicarse al bienestar de los demas Pitufos. Va a curarles de todos sus males...con la ayuda del malvado Gargamel!

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Es cierto: lo bueno en exceso puede ser malo. Cuando se produce un accidente que afecta a la formula magica de Papa Pitufo y este acaba duplicado, los Pitufos se muestran encantados: dos Papas Pitufo pueden dar el doble de buenos consejos y el doble de amor que uno solo. Sin embargo, despues de un tiempo, las cosas se complican en exceso en la aldea. ¡Sobre todo cuando otro accidente hace que Gargamel tambien se duplique!

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Papa Pitufo organiza un grupo para navegar a una lejana isla ya que Gargamel ha cortado todos los arboles menos uno para atrapar a los pitufos. Gargamel les sigue pero la Bruja de la isla acaba enviando sus gaviotas tras el.

programme.title: La Formula Aniquiladora
programme.desc: Existe una palabra magica aterradora. Cuando pronuncias esa palabra hacia algo o alguien, ¡haces que se desvanezca en la nada! ¿Podran los Pitufos anular su malvado poder antes de que Gargamel se apropie de ella?

programme.title: Pitufo Salvaje Ii
programme.desc: Cansados de lo que consideran la aburrida vida de la aldea, los Pitufitos se marchan y deciden ir a vivir con Pitufo Salvaje y Chitter. Mientras tanto, Gargamel ha tramado un terrible plan para acabar con los Pitufos...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Gargamel ha ideado un nuevo y diabolico plan para librarse de los Pitufos: un polvo brillante que hara que no puedan dejar de reirse...

programme.title: El Pitufo Enmascarado
programme.desc: Una noche de Luna Azulada, tal y como la leyenda decia, un bebe pitufo aparece en el pueblo, y todos acaban agarrandole carino. Pero todo ha sido un malentendido y la ciguena vuelve por el bebe. Pintor y Grunon se han encarinado tanto con el bebe que les regresan al bebe.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos conocen a un elfo del bosque, que les ensena la lengua de signos despues de que Gargamel les administre una pocion de enmudecimiento.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Practico aprende que es mejor haber pitufado que no haber pitufado nunca cuando descubre que su amor verdadero es una sirena. ¿Podran vivir juntos para siempre?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Sonador vera cumplido su deseo de ser un Astropitufo cuando Papa Pitufo le hechiza para quedarse dormido, transformando el paisaje y a los Pitufos en una fantasia galactica. Gargamel vigila de cerca las travesuras de los Pitufos desde su bola de cristal, pero el hechizo de Papa Pitufo tambien tiene efecto en el y le transporta hasta el centro de una tormenta.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Hogatha se disfraza de premio de oro para observar a los Pitufos y capturarlos para sus ingredientes de belleza. Vanidoso acaba convenciendola de que pruebe su receta y acaba cubierta de barro de vuelta a casa de Gargamel.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Un monstruo del pantano secuestra a Bebe Pitufo como regalo para una bruja. La bruja, que cree que nadie la ama, se sorprende cuando Bebe Pitufo le demuestra afecto. Cuando Papa Pitufo acude a rescatar a Bebe Pitufo, consigue que la bruja entienda que el leal monstruo del pantano siempre la ha amado.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Curioso ha tenido una idea: ¿por que no imprimir un boletin con todas las noticias de la aldea? Esta seguro de que sus cotilleos sobre los Pitufos interesaran a todos los lectores. Pero las cosas no salen exactamente segun lo previsto cuando Papa Pitufo encuentra superpitufrutas.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Filosofo esta horrorizado. Sasita no sabe leer, por lo que podria estar condenada a perderse las perlas de sabiduria que contiene su libro «Citas de Pitufo Filosofo». Asi pues, intenta ensenarla a leer. Sin embargo, resulta que casi lo primero que puede leer es una formula para hacer que todos los libros desaparezcan. Todos los libros del mundo, ¡incluidos el libro de hechizos de Gargamel y los libros de remedios de Omnibus!

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: Viaje Al Pitufo De La Tierra
programme.desc: El invierno ha llegado a la Aldea Pitufa. Y los pequenos Pitufos estan helados de frio. ¿Pero que esta haciendo Pitufo Torpe con esa extrana roca que ha descubierto? ¿Y por que esta tan entusiasmado Pitufo Minero con su nuevo descubrimiento? Nadie entiende a que se debe tanto revuelo por una simple nueva roca para la coleccion de Pitufo Torpe... Al adentrarse bajo tierra, los Pitufos encontraran peligros y sorpresas.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Mientras intenta escabullirse de sus tareas, Pitufo Perezoso encuentra un antiguo pozo abandonado con una interesante peculiaridad: cualquier objeto que uno baje en el cubo regresa como nuevo. Pero ¿es eso bueno?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Papa Pitufo recuerda las emocionantes aventuras de Sonador en el mar, con tortugas, ballenas, islas desiertas...y piratas!

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Gargamel ha echado tantas sustancias toxicas en su estanque que el agua se vuelve encantada. Tras caerse en el estanque, Gargamel se vuelve pequeno, tan pequeno que Papa Pitufo tendra que salvarlo.

programme.title: Poema Al Tiempo
programme.desc: Pitufo Carpintero, Pitufo Filosofo, Pitufo Torpe y Pitufina descubren el reloj de arena del tiempo en una cueva y empiezan a trastear con el, lo que provoca que el tiempo se descontrole para todos los Pitufos.

programme.title: Pitufos Y Solo Pitufos
programme.desc: El malvado mago Gargamel ha conseguido capturar a Pitufina. Ahora, se dispone a administrarle un suero de la verdad para descubrir todos los secretos de Papa Pitufo... pero Gargamel comete un gran error y le da a Pitufina una formula de las mentiras.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Papa Pitufo deja a los Pitufos reparando la presa del pueblo mientras el se va de excursion en busqueda de hierbas para sus pociones. Mientras esta fuera, Pitufo Filosofo provoca un revuelo al declarase a si mismo Rey y Papa Pitufo regresa a tiempo para evitar que la presa se destruya.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cuando en la Aldea Pitufa forman una brigada de incendios para combatir las llamas que devoran la cocina de Pitufo Goloso, se dan cuenta de que Gargamel les ha dejado sin agua. Sin embargo, no se da cuenta de la fragilidad de su presa, que se rompe y provoca que el agua arrastre a Gargamel y Azrael e inunde la Aldea Pitufa, extinguiendo el fuego.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Miedoso entra corriendo en la aldea y grita que el cielo se esta cayendo. Justo en ese mismo momento, Papa Pitufo esta aquejado de un incontrolable ataque de estornudos...

programme.title: La Pesadilla De Pitufo Sonador
programme.desc: Sonador se separa de la Aldea en busca de aventuras, pero termina en manos del malvado Gargamel. Papa Pitufo debera ir a su rescate.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Todos pueden cometer errores. Incluso Papa Pitufo. programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Unos lentes rosados llegan a manos de Pitufina y resultan ser un sucio truco de Gargamel.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cuando los Pitufos llegan a la antigua China, descubren que el emperador nino corre peligro de ser depuesto. ¿Y por quien? ¡Por el malvado Garg-Fu-Yun, que quiere hacerse con el trono del nino!

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Las pinturas del malvado Maestro son capaces de tele portar a sus modelos dentro del cuadro...para siempre! Papa pitufo le dice a Pintor que cambie las pinturas y en poco tiempo Maestro acaba dentro de uno de sus cuadros, al lado de su modelo de ensueno: Pitufina.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Sonador vera cumplido su deseo de ser un Astropitufo cuando Papa Pitufo le hechiza para quedarse dormido, transformando el paisaje y a los Pitufos en una fantasia galactica. Gargamel vigila de cerca las travesuras de los Pitufos desde su bola de cristal, pero el hechizo de Papa Pitufo tambien tiene efecto en el y le transporta hasta el centro de una tormenta.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: El malvado mago Gargamel vuelve a estar en problemas. Si no puede reunir una enorme cantidad de oro para el atardecer, le arrebataran todas sus posesiones. Sin embargo, los Pitufos van a ayudar a su archienemigo... hasta cierto punto.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: En las profundidades de la selva, los Pitufos se encuentran con un cazador de cabezas que les transforma en tontainas con la cabeza del tamano de un alfiler. Pitufo Torpe consigue escapar... y ahora le toca usar la cabeza.

programme.title: A Todas Las Criaturas Grandes Y Pequenas
programme.desc: Pitufo Natural esta convencido de que puede ayudar a todas las criaturas con sus dones curativos, incluso al malvado Azrael, cuya pata queda atrapada en una trampa. El gato se cura y, a pesar de que tiene la tentacion de quedarse con los Pitufos, regresa con Gargamel, pero conduce a su dueno hacia un lugar alejado de la Aldea Pitufa.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Posar para una escultura, sobre todo para una composicion enorme como la de Pitufo Pintor, es un trabajo agotador, y es imposible evitar moverse un poco. Ahora, Papa Pitufo ha encontrado la forma de que los modelos se queden completamente quietos. Sin embargo, tiene algunos inconvenientes, tal como los Pitufos comprobaran pronto...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los cristales magicos hacen que los Pitufos visiten todo tipo de lugares. Ahora se encuentran en la Antartida, volviendose aun mas azules por el frio, y Bebe Pitufo se ha resfriado. ¿Como podran escapar hacia un sitio mas calido?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Un hechizo de Papa Pitufo sale mal y convierte a un ave en una espantosa criatura que aterroriza la Aldea Pitufo.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufina descubre la maldad con el maligno plan de Chlorhydris de lanzar un hechizo de "mundo sin amor" al pozo magico de los deseos. ¡Es una carrera contrarreloj para que los Pitufos y Cupido puedan arreglar las cosas!

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: ¿Que es esa extrana rana parlante que ha hecho que el hechicero Morlock haya enviado a todos los soldados del principe Teodoro para capturarla? ¿Es una rana demonio, como el dice? ¿O quiza lo hace por otro motivo? La verdad se desvelara cuando Pitufina y los Pitufitos se encuentran con la rana. Ayudan a la rana a volver a transformarse en el principe Teodoro, que habia sido victima de un hechizo lanzado por Morlock.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Hay un premio para aquel Pitufo que tenga la mascota mas adorable. Bebe Pitufo acude con Carino Dorado, una mascota adorable y carinosa de la que todo el mundo se enamora. Sin embargo, esa mascota es una creacion del malvado mago Gargamel con la que pretende destruir a los Pitufos.
